Package com.stremebase.field

com.stremebase.field offers some basic high-level fields to be used at the data access layer.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MultiSetField<T>
    A field that that stores a multiset of values
    MultiSetField.MultiSetEntry<T>
    Includes the count of the value
    SerializableField<T extends Serializable>
    A field to store any serializable value.
    SetField<T>
    A field that stores a set of values
    StackField<T>
    A field to store a stack of values
    TagSetField<T,TT>
    A field to store a set where a tag can be associated with a value.
    TagSetField.TagSetEntry<T,TT>
    High level representation of the value and it's assoicated tag
    TextField
    A field to store and retrieve longer texts.
    TextField.TextIndex
    A simple utility class for indexing and querying documents (=texts=arrays of words).
    TupleField<T>
    The field to store a tuple of values
    VarField
    A field to store global database variables efficiently

Package com.stremebase.field Description

com.stremebase.field offers some basic high-level fields to be used at the data access layer.

Use their source codes as examples when writing your own domain specific fields.
